# Bandit Level 3 → Level 4

## Objective
Find and read a hidden file inside a directory.

## Concepts Learned
- Hidden files in Unix (prefixed with a dot .)
- Using ls -la to list all files, including hidden ones
- Navigating directories and reading file content

## Tools & Commands Introduced
- ls -la – list directory contents with details and hidden files
- cat – display file content

## Approach
1. Move into the target directory (inhere).
2. List all files, including hidden ones.
3. Identify the hidden file (prefixed with .).
4. Display its contents.

## Example Command
ls -la
cat .hidden_filename

## Key Takeaway
- Hidden files are a common way to store configuration or sensitive data.
- Always use ls -la when searching for files, not just ls.
